User will get an ERROR message *Sorry, your username and/or password are incorrect. Please try again.* in Confluence login screen if they are not exist in Confluence.

This will trigger the user to Click on *Forgot your password?* link and input their email address to reset the password. However, they will not receive any email to reset the password.

Therefore, it would be much convenience to improve the ERROR message saying that they are not allowed to login (username does not exist etc.) and they should contact Confluence Administrator.

h4. Steps to Reproduce:
# Install a fresh Confluence 5.10.7
# Restore a Cloud Backup
# Create / Edit pages

h4. Actual behavior:
Page spinning  forever and following error appears in logs:
{code}
2016-10-13 09:36:57,463 ERROR [http-nio-8090-exec-10] [confluence.plugins.synchrony.SynchronyContextProvider] getContextMap This instance could not be registered with Synchrony.
 -- space: 1638403 | url: /plugins/editor-loader/editor.action | page: 26705975 | traceId: 0d013bf225cda166 | userName: sysadmin | referer: http://localhost:8090/pages/viewpage.action?pageId=26705975 | action: editor
{code}

h4. Expected Behavior:

Since you can restore cloud backup into 5.10 and later _([here|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Migrate+from+Confluence+Cloud+to+Server])_ you should be able to edit and create pages 

h4. Workaround for Confluence 5.10):

# Navigate to {{<base URL>/admin/darkfeatures.action}}
# Remove:
## {{site-wide.synchrony}}
## {{site-wide.synchrony.opt-in}}
## {{site-wide.shared-drafts}}

h4. Workaround for Confluence 6.0+:
This issue does not affect customers on Confluence 6.0 or greater. If you are experiencing issues editing pages after upgrade, please see [Troubleshooting Collaborative Editing|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/troubleshooting-collaborative-editing-858772087.html]

