h5. Issue Summary

After migrating data over from Confluence Cloud to Server, all users or only certain users get an empty homepage/dashboard after logging in to Confluence as per screenshot below : 
!Screen Shot 2016-08-25 at 10.12.11.png|thumbnail! 

This issue was caused by a Confluence Cloud specific dark feature called {{react.ui.dashboard}} :
 !Screen Shot 2016-08-29 at 11.06.42 PM.png|thumbnail! 

h5. Workaround
If all users were affected :
# Kindly log into Confluence Server as an administrator
# Access URL {{<base-url>/admin/darkfeatures.action}}
# Kindly scroll to the *Site Dark Features* section
# Remove {{react.ui.dashboard}}

If only certain users were affected :
# Kindly log into Confluence Server as the affected user
# Access URL {{<base-url>/users/darkfeatures.action}}
# Kindly scroll to the *User Dark Features* section
# Remove {{react.ui.dashboard}}

Please use the following database query to verify if there's any other user affected by this issue :
{code:sql}
SELECT lower_username from user_mapping where USER_KEY IN (SELECT TRIM(LEADING 'USERPROPS-' FROM entity_name) FROM OS_PROPERTYENTRY WHERE STRING_VAL LIKE '%react.ui.dashboard%');
{code}

